[SN]TITLE[SN]
Scott Harrison: Defender rejoins Hartlepool after leaving in May

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Hartlepool United have re-signed centre-back Scott Harrison after releasing him in May.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Harrison, who began his career at Darlington, first joined Pools on loan from Sunderland in March 2014 before joining permanently in February 2015.
The 22-year-old has been training at the League Two club over the summer and has played in several pre-season games.
Harrison, who was Hartlepool's Player of the Year in 2014, has scored twice in 70 appearances for the club.
